HOUSE JOINT RESOLUTION 283
By Clemmons
A RESOLUTION to honor and congratulate Deborah E. Whitman
on her selection as the 2024–2025 Metro
Nashville Public Schools Support Employee of
the Year.
WHEREAS, it is fitting that the members of this General Assembly should pause to
specially recognize those outstanding professionals who have devoted their careers to providing
the highest quality educational environment for Tennessee's students; and
WHEREAS, Deborah E. Whitman is one such estimable individual, who has
distinguished herself as a professional of the greatest dedication, ability, and integrity; and
WHEREAS, an attendance clerk at Tusculum Elementary School, Ms. Whitman has
recently been named the 2024–2025 Metro Nashville Public Schools Support Employee of the
Year, a most befitting honor that recognizes the positive influence she has on so many young
lives; and
WHEREAS, Ms. Whitman is an extremely talented and compassionate professional who
works assiduously to motivate her school's students to reach their full potential, both as scholars
and as citizens; and
WHEREAS, Ms. Whitman serves as an inspiration to colleagues and students alike, and
her friendship and counsel are highly valued by those who are fortunate to know her; and
WHEREAS, Deborah Whitman truly epitomizes the dedicated professional who is wholly
committed to the highest ideals of public service and quality education for all, and she should be
specially recognized; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF THE ONE HUNDRED
FOURTEENTH GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE SENATE
CONCURRING, that we hereby honor and congratulate Deborah E. Whitman on being chosen
as the 2024–2025 Metro Nashville Public Schools Support Employee of the Year, commend her
